 show that there are blocks of m primes for any m\nsuch that all gaps between these primes simultaneously satisfy the lower\nestimate Clognloglognloglogloglogn/(logloglogn)^2 with an arbitrarily large\nconstant C. The proof uses the method of Maynard.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Jul 2014 18:52:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 24 Sep 2014 16:30:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-09-25"}
