direction and the\nplanet's temperature. Such a correlation could arise if thermal emission\ndominates light from hotter planets that harbor hot spots shifted toward the\nevening-side, as theoretically predicted, while reflected light dominates\ncooler planets with clouds on the planet's morning-side.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Jul 2014 20:00:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 May 2015 22:57:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-27"}
